Is there a way to override the styling ONLY for a single element of an embedded form?
Example:
```&lt;!--[if lte IE 8]&gt;
&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/v2-legacy.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;![endif]--&gt;
&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/v2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  hbspt.forms.create({
	portalId: "XXXXX",
	formId: "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX",
    cssRequired: ".submitted-message{color:#fff}"
});
&lt;/script&gt;```
I just want to change the color of the submitted message.. how can I do that?
